@startuml
title Security-Focused Sequence Diagram: Development Machine Deployment

actor Developer
participant "GitHub Actions" as GHA
participant "AWS OIDC/Credentials" as Auth
participant "CloudFormation" as CF
participant "IAM Service" as IAM
participant "EC2 Service" as EC2
participant "Security Group" as SG
participant "EC2 Instance" as Instance
participant "CloudWatch" as CW

Developer -> GHA: Push code/trigger workflow
activate GHA

GHA -> Auth: Request AWS credentials
activate Auth
note right of Auth: Security Risk: Broad credentials\nShould use OIDC provider
Auth --> GHA: Return AWS credentials
deactivate Auth

GHA -> CF: Deploy CloudFormation stack
activate CF

CF -> IAM: Create IAM Role
activate IAM
note right of IAM: Security Risk: AdministratorAccess policy\nViolates least privilege principle
IAM --> CF: Role created with AdministratorAccess
deactivate IAM

CF -> IAM: Create Instance Profile
activate IAM
IAM -> IAM: Attach AdministratorAccess role
IAM --> CF: Instance Profile created
deactivate IAM

CF -> SG: Create Security Group
activate SG
note right of SG: Security Risk: SSH from 0.0.0.0/0\nShould restrict to trusted IPs
SG -> SG: Allow SSH (port 22) from 0.0.0.0/0
SG --> CF: Security Group configured
deactivate SG

CF -> EC2: Launch EC2 instance
activate EC2
EC2 -> Instance: Create instance with parameters
activate Instance

EC2 -> Instance: Attach Instance Profile (AdministratorAccess)
note right of Instance: Instance has full AWS account access\nMajor security vulnerability

EC2 -> Instance: Apply Security Group rules
Instance --> EC2: Instance launched
deactivate Instance
EC2 --> CF: Instance created
deactivate EC2

CF -> CW: Create CloudWatch Alarm
activate CW
note right of CW: Inactivity alarm for cost optimization\nStops instance after 1 hour idle
CW --> CF: Alarm configured
deactivate CW

CF --> GHA: Stack deployed successfully
deactivate CF

GHA --> Developer: Deployment complete
deactivate GHA

== Instance Access Phase ==

Developer -> Instance: SSH connection attempt
activate Instance
Instance -> SG: Validate incoming connection
activate SG
SG -> SG: Check source IP against rules (0.0.0.0/0)
note right of SG: Any IP address accepted\nNo IP restriction enforcement
SG --> Instance: Connection allowed
deactivate SG

Instance --> Developer: SSH access granted
note left of Developer: Developer has shell access\nwith AdministratorAccess privileges

Developer -> Instance: Execute AWS CLI commands
Instance -> IAM: Use Instance Profile credentials
activate IAM
IAM -> IAM: Validate AdministratorAccess permissions
IAM --> Instance: Full AWS permissions granted
deactivate IAM
Instance --> Developer: Command executed with admin rights

deactivate Instance

== Inactivity Monitoring ==

CW -> Instance: Monitor CPU utilization
activate CW
activate Instance
CW -> CW: Detect < 10% CPU for 1 hour
CW -> EC2: Trigger stop instance action
activate EC2
EC2 -> Instance: Stop instance
Instance --> EC2: Instance stopped
deactivate Instance
EC2 --> CW: Action completed
deactivate EC2
deactivate CW

@enduml
